### Module 5 — Caching Headers
### Use curl -v or -I to see response headers. VS Code REST Client also shows headers.

@base = http://localhost:3000

# ─── SPRINT: Cache-Control ───────────────────────────────

### Public cache (60s) — check Cache-Control header
GET {{base}}/public-data

### Private cache — CDN won't cache this
GET {{base}}/private-data

### No store — nothing caches this
GET {{base}}/sensitive-data

###
# curl -I http://localhost:3000/public-data
# curl -I http://localhost:3000/private-data
# curl -I http://localhost:3000/sensitive-data


# ─── DEEP DIVE: ETag ─────────────────────────────────────

### Step 1: First request — observe the ETag header in the response
GET {{base}}/posts

### Step 2: Copy the ETag value from Step 1, paste it below.
###         If content hasn't changed → 304 Not Modified (no body!)
GET {{base}}/posts
If-None-Match: "PASTE_ETAG_HERE"

###
# Step 1 - get the etag:
# curl -v http://localhost:3000/posts 2>&1 | grep -i etag
#
# Step 2 - use it:
# curl -v http://localhost:3000/posts -H 'If-None-Match: "the-etag-value"'
# You should see: < HTTP/1.1 304 Not Modified


# ─── DEEP DIVE: Last-Modified ────────────────────────────

### Step 1: First request — observe Last-Modified header
GET {{base}}/posts/by-date

### Step 2: Send the date back — should get 304
GET {{base}}/posts/by-date
If-Modified-Since: Mon, 15 Jan 2024 10:00:00 GMT

### Step 3: Send an older date — should get 200 (content is newer)
GET {{base}}/posts/by-date
If-Modified-Since: Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 GMT

###
# curl -v http://localhost:3000/posts/by-date 2>&1 | grep -i "last-modified"
# curl -v http://localhost:3000/posts/by-date \
#   -H "If-Modified-Since: Mon, 15 Jan 2024 10:00:00 GMT"


# ─── DEEP DIVE: stale-while-revalidate ──────────────────

### Check the Cache-Control header
GET {{base}}/news


# ─── No headers (dangerous default) ────────────────────

GET {{base}}/no-headers
